§7§oThis gate works like an AND gate that saves state over time.

The output side is the one with a torch. The side opposite to it is the reset, and the two sides with the square lamps are the inputs.

If one of the inputs receives a signal, the corresponding light will turn on.

The output will produce a pulse after both lights are turned on.

If a redstone signal is applied to the reset side, it will turn off both lights.
